title: For Sale:  ED BROWN SPECIAL FORCES 1911 -- .45 ACP...GEN4 BLACK...MINT !
postcontent:
Here's a super high quality 1911 pistol from one of the most respected builders in the trade. Manufactured by Ed Brown, this is a "Special Forces" .45 auto. Built simply with serious performance and reliability in mind, the Special Forces does not have a lot of fancy bells and whistles. There is no light rail, no full length guide rod, nor any front serrations...nothing you don't absolutely need. Slide to frame fit is excellent, of course. The trigger is excellent, of course. It features the "Chainlink I" treatment to the front strap and flat mainspring housing. An Ed Brown beavertail grip safety with memory groove is standard, as are the 3-hole long trigger, and skeletonized commander hammer. The ambidextrous tactical safety was a custom order extra. It is fitted with high visibility three dot tritium night sights (dated 2013) and is factory finished in the super durable Gen4 black coating which offers extremely good corrosion and wear resistance. Grips are diamond checkered laminated wood.
Condition is excellent, virtually brand new, and I'd grade this pistol at better than 99%. It appears that it has been test fired only. There is no external wear and looking at the breech face it would appear that very few rounds have been fired. Needless to say, the mechanics are in perfect working order and the bore is excellent. It comes in the Ed Brown black range bag with one Ed Brown 7-round stainless magazine with bumper. The owner's manual, safety lock, allen wrench and lube are included. Just a SUPER NICE that anyone would be proud to own!!
